The Nigeria First Foundation (NFF) has urged delegates to elect only pan-Nigeria presidential candidates. It appealed to delegates of the All Progressives Congress (APC) and the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to put the interest of the country above ethnic, religious and other primordial considerations while electing their standard-bearers.   Ex-Minister, Senator emerge Kwara PDP senatorial candidates     Gombe Central: Goje denies participating in PDP primary,â€¦     2023: Ned Nwoko wins PDP Senate ticket for Delta North   The Chairman of the board of the NFF, Sir Mike Okiro, in an interactive session with members in Nigeria and in the diaspora, said the situation in the country required nationalistic approach from the delegates. Okiro, a former Inspector General of Police and ex-chairman of the Police Service Commission, advised the delegates to vote for candidates who could address the hydra headed challenges confronting the country.